formula: E.g.f. log(1 + A(x)) with the e.g.f. A(x):=exp(x/2)*sinh(sqrt(5)*x/2)/(sqrt(5)/2) of A000045.

a(n) ~ -(n-1)! / r^n, where r = -1.37807491378452630283968362340785266756... is the root of the equation abs(2*(5-3*sqrt(5))*r + (sqrt(5)-5) * (log(5/4) + 2*log(1-coth(sqrt(5)*r/2)))) = 0. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Sep 04 2014
